  <bioghist id="aspace_45c63bb3acea2ba4be9232c97bfb2ab8">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Cornell University Library employees, 1955-1971.</p><p> Born Hungary, displaced persons after the Second World War. Both Ph.D.s, Rome.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_1d917e38d20bf3905d24104f8128b3b1">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Personal papers of the Mayer sisters Helena and Elizabeth include correspondence, photographs, diaries, manuscripts of novels and short stories, and documents pertaining to their status as students, displaced persons, scholars, and naturalized American citizens. Includes academic reading notes, scholarly articles, diplomas and certificates, art work, ephemera (keepsakes, coins), and postcards, financial material, retirement documents, family records, and miscellaneous other papers.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_031ac1344bcfd25d724bc7e0b056c426">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Helena and Elizabeth Mayer papers, #4938. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
